def_cn: (用作动词或介词宾语，与句子主语指代同一个人)我自己
def_en: A speaker or writer uses myself to refer to himself or herself. Myself is used as the object of a verb or preposition when the subject refers to the same person.

def_cn: (用于强调第一人称单数主语)我本人，我自己
def_en: You use myself to emphasize a first person singular subject. In more formal English, myself is sometimes used instead of 'me' as the object of a verb or preposition, for emphasis.
If you say something such as 'I did it myself', you are emphasizing that you did it, rather than anyone else.
